Description: Almost complete clay seal-impression bearing two seal impression of an oval scarab-like seal. The rear of the sealing shows two small rows of basketry coil that turn into one larger on one side and the other side shows plant fibres like from a basket but the side is flat, maybe a lid. The seal itself shows two signs next to each other like wDA (U28) but with each two lines underneath. Right of this a standing falcon facing to the left. Behind the falcon an upright uraeus. A second impression of the same seal underneath but bare recognisable except for the falcon.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
